# Layout settings

# Whitespace will be ignored (Spaces and tabs)
# Each line is one element
# Values are not separated by anything, just the known length of the type

# Types:
# The first character of a line is a type. Case doesn't matter.

# '#' Comment
# Ignores line.

# '?' Settings <width: ####, height: ####, scale: ###, corner radius: ###, spacing: ##, font: "">
# Only the first settings will be used.

# 'S' Section <pos x: ##, pos y: ##, width: ##, height: ##, title: "", font size: ##>
# Sections are designed to hold other UI elements and divide them into categories.
# Sections will be one unit taller to fit the title.

# I didn't know how to make inputs useful enough, while still having them replacable.
# My solution was having inputs run an external executable.

# 'B' Button <pos x: ##, pos y: ##, width: ##, height: ##, label: "", font size: ##, exec: "">
# Buttons run <exec> when clicked.

# 'T' Toggle <pos x: ##, pos y: ##, width: ##, height: ##, label: "", font size: ##, exec: "">
# Toggles also need to have a "Q_"<exec> file that will be run on startup and click.
# Toggles run <exec> when clicked, then "Q_"<exec>. "Q_"<exec> should return 1 or 0.

# 'X' Textbox <pos x: ##, pos y: ##, width: ##, height: ##, text: "", font size: ##>
# Just displays text, no interaction.

# 'C': Color <hex front: RRGGBB, hex back: RRGGBB, hex text: RRGGBB>
# Sets the colors of elements created after it.


